### Phase 3 — Execution Service smoke tests
###
### These hit the webhook + actuator endpoints directly. The 4 gRPC RPCs
### (SubmitCode, GetExecutionResult, GetExecutionResultsBatch, ListLanguages)
### get exercised by App Service in Phase 4 and by a standalone gRPC client
### during Phase 3 verification (see roadmap §Phase 3 checkpoint).
###
### Prerequisites:
###   - Judge0 reachable via `make judge0-tunnel` (Phase 2)
###   - Postgres up:    docker compose -f infra/docker/docker-compose.execution.yml up -d
###   - Service up:     mvn -pl execution-service spring-boot:run
###

### 1. Health
GET http://localhost:8081/actuator/health

### 2. Webhook — simulate Judge0 callback (replace {{token}} with a real one).
###    Use this to verify the webhook handler updates the row even without a
###    real Judge0 callback firing.
PUT http://localhost:8081/webhook/judge0/{{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "token": "{{token}}",
  "stdout": "hello\n",
  "stderr": null,
  "compile_output": null,
  "time": "0.012",
  "memory": 3520,
  "exit_code": 0,
  "status": { "id": 3, "description": "Accepted" }
}

### 3. Webhook — runtime error variant
PUT http://localhost:8081/webhook/judge0/{{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "token": "{{token}}",
  "stdout": null,
  "stderr": "ZeroDivisionError: division by zero\n",
  "compile_output": null,
  "time": "0.008",
  "memory": 3300,
  "exit_code": 1,
  "status": { "id": 11, "description": "Runtime Error (NZEC)" }
}

### 4. Webhook — unknown token (expect 404)
PUT http://localhost:8081/webhook/judge0/does-not-exist
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": { "id": 3, "description": "Accepted" }
}


### 5. Generate a REAL token via gRPC
GRPC localhost:9091/codearena.execution.v1.ExecutionService/SubmitCode

{
  "user_id": "test-user-123",
  "language_id": 71,
  "source_code": "print('Hello from gRPC test!')"
}